"""Whirlpool Hash Function — ISO/IEC 10118-3, NESSIE final (2003).

Implements the Whirlpool hash algorithm (NESSIE final / ISO 10118-3 §13).
Produces a 512-bit (64-byte) digest.

Design:
  - Miyaguchi-Preneel wide-pipe compression over 64-byte blocks.
  - 10-round AES-like block cipher W with 8×8 byte-matrix state.
  - Round function: AddRoundKey(MixRows(ShiftColumns(SubBytes(state))), K[r]).
  - Key schedule: K[0] = H_prev; K[r] = round_function(K[r-1], RC[r]).
  - Cipher: eta[0] = M XOR H; eta[r] = round_function(eta[r-1], K[r]).
  - Output: H_new = eta[10] XOR H XOR M  (Miyaguchi-Preneel).
  - IV = all-zero 64-byte state.
  - Padding: append 0x80, zero-pad to ≡32 (mod 64), append 256-bit big-endian
    bit-count (32 bytes). The length encoding is 32 bytes, NOT 8 (unlike SHA-2).

References:
  ISO/IEC 10118-3:2004 §13 (Whirlpool hash function).
  P. S. L. M. Barreto, V. Rijmen — "The Whirlpool Hashing Function" (2003).
  https://www.larc.usp.br/~pbarreto/whirlpool.zip (reference implementation).
"""

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# rt_bytes_u8_at extern — indexed access into [u8] arrays
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

extern fn rt_bytes_u8_at(arr: [u8], idx: i64) -> i64

fn _u8_at(buf: [u8], idx: u64) -> u8:
    rt_bytes_u8_at(buf, idx.to_i64()).to_u8()

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Whirlpool S-box (E table) — ISO/IEC 10118-3 §13.7.
# 256 bytes; S[i] gives the substituted byte for input i.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

